Construct a 6 block by 6 block square.

Then, construct a horizontal line with 5 blocks to the bottom of the square.
row(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ bottom_side(a, d, 2) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the horizontal line's left end is next to the third column of the square.

rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 6) ^ width(a, 5)
Form a rectangle that is 5 blocks wide and 6 blocks tall.
row(b) ^ width(b, 8) ^ rectangle(a) ^ top(b, a)
Then, build a horizontal line with 8 blocks to the top of the rectangle.
row(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_right(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the horizontal line's right end is adjacent to the rectangle's upper right corner.

Form a 2 block by 2 block square.
row(b) ^ width(b, 7) ^ square(a) ^ left(b, a)
After that, create a horizontal line of size 7 to the left of the square.
row(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the horizontal line's right end is next to the upper left corner of the square.

===
rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 2) ^ width(a, 7)
Construct a 7 by 2 rectangle.
column(b) ^ height(b, 5) ^ rectangle(a) ^ right(b, a)
After that, build a column with 5 blocks to the right of the rectangle.
column(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ lower_right(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(east, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the column's bottom end is adjacent to the lower right corner of the rectangle.

Create a row of size 7.

Then, build a vertical line with 4 blocks to the top of the row.
column(b) ^ row(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 3) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the bottom end of the vertical line is adjacent to the fourth column of the row.

After that, construct a horizontal line of size 8 to the top of the rectangle.

Ensure that the rectangle's upper right corner is next to the seventh row of the square.

row(a) ^ width(a, 4)
Form a row using 4 blocks.
column(b) ^ height(b, 3) ^ row(a) ^ top(b, a)
Then, form a vertical line of size 3 to the top of the row.
column(b) ^ row(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 1) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the bottom end of the vertical line is adjacent to the second column of the row.

===
rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 3) ^ width(a, 4)
Construct a 4 by 3 rectangle.
row(b) ^ width(b, 6) ^ rectangle(a) ^ top(b, a)
After that, create a row of size 6 to the top of the rectangle.
row(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 1) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the right end of the row is adjacent to the second column of the rectangle.

Ensure that the sixth row of the rectangle is next to the row's right end.

rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 2) ^ width(a, 10)
Form a rectangle that is 2 blocks tall and 10 blocks wide.
rectangle(b) ^ height(b, 3) ^ width(b, 6) ^ rectangle(a) ^ bottom(b, a)
Next, create another one that is 3 blocks tall and 6 blocks wide to the bottom of the first one.
rectangle(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ lower_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the upper left corner of this rectangle is in line with the lower left corner of the first rectangle.

Ensure that the left end of the horizontal line is adjacent to the lower right corner of the square.

Build a square with sides of block length 3.
row(b) ^ width(b, 8) ^ square(a) ^ left(b, a)
Next, form a row with 8 blocks to the left of the square.
row(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the row's right end is in line with the upper left corner of the square.

Ensure that the upper right corner of the square is in line with the third row of the vertical line.

Next, form another one with sides of block length 10 to the left of the first one.
square(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ left_side(a, d, 1) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the upper right corner of this square is adjacent to the second row of the first square.

===
row(a) ^ width(a, 7)
Create a horizontal line using 7 blocks.
square(b) ^ size(b, 4) ^ row(a) ^ right(b, a)
Next, construct a square with sides of block length 4 to the right of the horizontal line.
square(b) ^ row(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ left_side(b, c, 1) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_right(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(east, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the second row of the square is adjacent to the right end of the horizontal line.

===
rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 9) ^ width(a, 7)
Create a 7 by 9 rectangle.
rectangle(b) ^ height(b, 5) ^ width(b, 8) ^ rectangle(a) ^ left(b, a)
After that, create another one that is 5 blocks tall and 8 blocks wide to the left of the first one.
rectangle(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the lower right corner of the new rectangle is next to the upper left corner of the first rectangle.

After that, construct a 3 by 4 rectangle to the bottom of the square.

Ensure that the upper left corner of the rectangle is next to the third column of the square.

Next, build a rectangle that is 9 blocks wide and 6 blocks tall to the top of the square.

Ensure that the second column of the rectangle is adjacent to the upper left corner of the square.

Then, create a row of size 5 to the right of the square.
row(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ right_side(a, d, 2) ^ spatial-rel(east, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the row's left end is adjacent to the third row of the square.

column(a) ^ height(a, 10)
Construct a vertical line with 10 blocks.
column(b) ^ height(b, 9) ^ column(a) ^ left(b, a)
Next, build another one of height 9 to the left of the first one.
column(b) ^ column(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ left_side(a, d, 7) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the bottom end of the column is next to the eighth row of the vertical line.

Ensure that the square's lower right corner is next to the second column of the horizontal line.

column(a) ^ height(a, 8)
Create a column using 8 blocks.
rectangle(b) ^ height(b, 5) ^ width(b, 3) ^ column(a) ^ top(b, a)
After that, form a rectangle that is 5 blocks tall and 3 blocks wide to the top of the column.
rectangle(b) ^ column(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ bottom_side(b, c, 1) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the second column of the rectangle is adjacent to the column's top end.

Then, construct a 10 by 6 rectangle to the right of the column.
rectangle(b) ^ column(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ lower_right(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(east, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the lower left corner of the rectangle is adjacent to the column's bottom end.

Then, construct another one of size 4 to the bottom of the first one.

Ensure that the left end of this horizontal line is adjacent to the sixth column of the first horizontal line.

Then, create a column of height 9 to the right of the horizontal line.

Ensure that the sixth row of the column is next to the horizontal line's right end.

Ensure that the seventh column of the new rectangle is next to the first rectangle's lower left corner.

row(b) ^ width(b, 10) ^ square(a) ^ bottom(b, a)
Next, form a horizontal line using 10 blocks to the bottom of the square.
row(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ bottom_side(a, d, 1) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the horizontal line's right end is adjacent to the second column of the square.

After that, build another one using 8 blocks to the right of the first one.
column(b) ^ column(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ right_side(a, d, 2) ^ spatial-rel(east, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the column's bottom end is next to the third row of the vertical line.

Ensure that the third row of the rectangle is adjacent to the upper right corner of the square.

===

Create a 5 block by 5 block square.

Then, create a rectangle with a width of 8 blocks and a height of 2 blocks to the bottom of the square.
rectangle(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ bottom_side(a, d, 1) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the upper left corner of the rectangle is next to the second column of the square.

square(a) ^ size(a, 7)
Form a 7 by 7 square.
rectangle(b) ^ height(b, 6) ^ width(b, 5) ^ square(a) ^ bottom(b, a)
After that, create a rectangle that is 5 blocks wide and 6 blocks tall to the bottom of the square.
rectangle(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ bottom_side(a, d, 3) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the rectangle's upper left corner is next to the fourth column of the square.

Ensure that the upper right corner of the rectangle is adjacent to the sixth row of the square.

===
rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 2) ^ width(a, 8)
Build a rectangle with a height of 2 blocks and a width of 8 blocks.
square(b) ^ size(b, 9) ^ rectangle(a) ^ top(b, a)
Next, create a 9 by 9 square to the top of the rectangle.
square(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 6) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the square's lower left corner is next to the seventh column of the rectangle.

Ensure that the horizontal line's right end is adjacent to the second row of the column.

Construct a horizontal line of size 5.
square(b) ^ size(b, 2) ^ row(a) ^ left(b, a)
Then, construct a 2 by 2 square to the left of the horizontal line.
square(b) ^ row(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the upper right corner of the square is adjacent to the left end of the horizontal line.

Ensure that the upper right corner of the square is next to the second row of the rectangle.

Ensure that the column's bottom end is adjacent to the fourth column of the rectangle.

Build a rectangle with a width of 2 blocks and a height of 5 blocks.
rectangle(b) ^ height(b, 3) ^ width(b, 2) ^ rectangle(a) ^ left(b, a)
After that, create another one with a height of 3 blocks and a width of 2 blocks to the left of the first one.
rectangle(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the upper right corner of the new rectangle is next to the upper left corner of the first rectangle.

Ensure that the second column of the new square is adjacent to the upper left corner of the first square.

column(a) ^ height(a, 4)
Create a column using 4 blocks.
row(b) ^ width(b, 8) ^ column(a) ^ bottom(b, a)
After that, form a row of length 8 to the bottom of the column.
row(b) ^ column(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ top_side(b, c, 1) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ lower_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(south, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the second column of the row is adjacent to the column's bottom end.

Next, construct a square with sides of block length 8 to the top of the rectangle.
square(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 2) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the lower right corner of the square is next to the third column of the rectangle.

After that, form a rectangle that is 2 blocks wide and 3 blocks tall to the bottom of the square.

Ensure that the rectangle's upper right corner is adjacent to the square's lower left corner.

column(b) ^ height(b, 4) ^ square(a) ^ top(b, a)
Then, build a column of size 4 to the top of the square.
column(b) ^ square(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_right(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the column's bottom end is adjacent to the square's upper right corner.

After that, form another one that is 6 blocks wide and 10 blocks tall to the top of the first one.
rectangle(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ lower_left(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ top_side(a, d, 3) ^ spatial-rel(north, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the lower left corner of the new rectangle is adjacent to the fourth column of the first rectangle.

===
rectangle(a) ^ height(a, 5) ^ width(a, 9)
Form a rectangle that is 5 blocks tall and 9 blocks wide.
column(b) ^ height(b, 6) ^ rectangle(a) ^ left(b, a)
After that, form a vertical line using 6 blocks to the left of the rectangle.
column(b) ^ rectangle(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ upper_right(b, c) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ left_side(a, d, 2) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the top end of the vertical line is adjacent to the third row of the rectangle.

Ensure that the row's left end is in line with the top end of the column.

Next, form a 7 by 7 square to the left of the horizontal line.
square(b) ^ row(a) ^ block(c) ^ location(w1) ^ block-location(c, w1) ^ right_side(b, c, 1) ^ block(d) ^ location(w2) ^ block-location(d, w2) ^ upper_left(a, d) ^ spatial-rel(west, 0, w2, w1)
Ensure that the second row of the square is next to the horizontal line's left end.
